Update CH4 emissions: Retire EDGAR v4.3.2 and replace with EDGAR v6.0

The EDGAR CH4 emissions have been updated to v6.0. Monthly sector-specific
emissions were downloaded from https://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/dataset_ghg60.
The script used to process these files for use in HEMCO and GEOS-Chem can be
found at http://ftp.as.harvard.edu/gcgrid/data/ExtData/HEMCO/CH4/v2022-01/EDGARv6/EDGARv6_CH4_edit.sh.

Signed-off-by: Melissa Sulprizio <mpayer@seas.harvard.edu>

GimmeThesaurus now supports Linked Data browsing. 

To enable it you need the following lines in httpd.conf
{{{
RewriteEngine on
RewriteRule ^/gemet/concept/([0-9]+)   http://www.eionet.europa.eu/gemet/concept?ns=1&cp=$1 [R]
RewriteRule ^/gemet/supergroup/([0-9]+)   http://www.eionet.europa.eu/gemet/concept?ns=2&cp=$1 [R]
RewriteRule ^/gemet/group/([0-9]+)   http://www.eionet.europa.eu/gemet/concept?ns=3&cp=$1 [R]     
RewriteRule ^/gemet/theme/([0-9]+)   http://www.eionet.europa.eu/gemet/concept?ns=4&cp=$1 [R]     
}}}
The you can give a concept url like http://www.eionet.europa.eu/gemet/concept/632 to the linked data browser.

Example: http://www4.wiwiss.fu-berlin.de/rdf_browser/?browse_uri=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eionet.europa.eu%2Fgemet%2Fconcept%2F632

Optimize PAdES-LT signature

Add only the needed revocation data for CC and CMD signatures: only for
signing certs. It works to extend existing signatures even using other
kinds of certificates as long as the direct issuer of the signing cert
is present in the EU Trusted List:
https://webgate.ec.europa.eu/tl-browser
